---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Content Rights — SFCE Learning App"
  description="Content rights and third-party content notices for the SFCE Learning native app for iPhone, iPad, and Mac."
  canonicalPath="/app/content-rights/"
  footerVariant="app"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-2">Content Rights and Third-Party Content</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary mb-8">
      <strong class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> May 8, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This document explains what content is included in the SFCE Learning app, what content is
        linked from external sources, and how third-party rights are handled.
      </p>
      <p>
        This document is provided for transparency and is not legal advice.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Summary</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning is an independent study tool for developers preparing for the Symfony
          certification exam.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">The app has the necessary rights to the content it includes because:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>The study guide structure, topic organization, progress experience, and quiz database are original SFCE Learning content or are used under the applicable project license.</li>
          <li>The guide includes curated links to external Symfony documentation and related technical resources instead of republishing those external pages inside the app.</li>
          <li>Symfony documentation is published under the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported License.</li>
          <li>Symfony source code is published under the MIT License.</li>
          <li>The app uses the word "Symfony" descriptively to identify the framework, documentation, and certification topic it helps users study.</li>
          <li>SFCE Learning is not affiliated with, endorsed by, sponsored by, or officially connected to Symfony SAS or SensioLabs.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Study Guide Content</h2>
        <p>
          The study guide is available without the quiz unlock. It organizes Symfony certification
          preparation into Symfony versions, topics, chapters, and reference links.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The guide is intended to help users navigate public documentation and track their learning
          progress. It does not claim ownership of Symfony, PHP, public technical facts, official
          documentation, or general programming concepts.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The selection, organization, metadata, user experience, and compiled guide structure are
          part of SFCE Learning's authored product, except where a source repository or third-party
          license states otherwise.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">External Documentation Links</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning includes curated reference links to external documentation and technical
          resources. These links open in an in-app browser or in the user's system browser.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The app does not copy or republish the full Symfony documentation pages as app content.
          External websites remain operated by their respective owners and are governed by their own
          licenses, terms, and privacy practices.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          For Symfony documentation, Symfony states that the documentation is licensed under
          Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0). That license permits
          sharing and adaptation under its attribution and share-alike conditions.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Source:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/contributing/documentation/license.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline break-all">https://symfony.com/doc/current/contributing/documentation/license.html</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Symfony Code and Documentation Licenses</h2>
        <p>Symfony publishes licensing information for its main materials:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Symfony documentation: Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported.</li>
          <li>Symfony source code: MIT License.</li>
          <li>Symfony website content: generally Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported unless stated otherwise.</li>
          <li>Symfony trademarks and logos: governed by Symfony's Trademark and Logo Policy.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Source:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/license" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">https://symfony.com/license</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Symfony Trademarks</h2>
        <p>
          "Symfony" is a trademark of Symfony SAS. SFCE Learning uses the name "Symfony" only to
          describe the framework, documentation, and certification subject that the app helps users
          study.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning does not present itself as an official Symfony product, official Symfony
          certification provider, official Symfony training provider, or product endorsed by Symfony
          SAS or SensioLabs.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning does not use Symfony logos unless separate written permission has been
          obtained from the appropriate rights holder.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Symfony's trademark policy is published here:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/trademark" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">https://symfony.com/trademark</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Quiz Content</h2>
        <p>
          The Knowledge Quiz is the only part of the app placed behind an in-app purchase.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Quiz questions, answer options, explanations, and related quiz material are original study
          content authored for SFCE Learning. They are provided for personal study use inside the
          app.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Users may not copy, scrape, reproduce, republish, redistribute, sell, or use the quiz
          question and answer database to create another product or dataset without written
          permission from the developer.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This restriction does not claim ownership of Symfony, PHP, public technical facts,
          official documentation, or general programming concepts. Some simple questions and answers
          may naturally resemble common technical explanations or publicly known facts. The
          restriction applies to the authored wording, selection, structure, and quiz database as a
          compiled product.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">App Store Connect Content Rights</h2>
        <p>
          For App Store Connect's "Content Rights" question, SFCE Learning can answer:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 italic">
          "Yes, this app has the necessary rights to its third-party content."
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">The basis for that answer is:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Third-party documentation is primarily referenced through external links, not copied wholesale into the app.</li>
          <li>Symfony documentation is publicly licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0 for sharing and adaptation under license conditions.</li>
          <li>Symfony code is publicly licensed under the MIT License.</li>
          <li>The app's paid quiz database is original SFCE Learning content.</li>
          <li>Symfony trademark use in the app metadata is descriptive and accompanied by a non-affiliation disclaimer.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Non-Affiliation Statement</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning is an independent study tool and is not affiliated with, endorsed by,
          sponsored by, or officially connected to Symfony SAS, SensioLabs, or the official Symfony
          Certification program.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Symfony is a trademark of Symfony SAS. Other names, trademarks, and logos belong to their
          respective owners.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="pt-4">
        See also the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}app/privacy-policy/`} class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>
        and <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}app/support/`} class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">Support</a> pages.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
